# Day teaching primer (kids_math)

## When this applies

- Editing **`lib/content/teachingPrimerCatalog.ts`** or optional **`teachingSummary` / `teachingSteps`** on `DayConcept`.
- Changing **`DayTeachingPrimer`**, TTS engine, or `TapToPlayTtsButton`.

## UI modules

- `components/teaching-primer/DayTeachingPrimer.tsx` — hub panel + chunked TTS.
- `lib/content/buildDayPrimerSpeakText.ts` — `buildDayPrimerSpeakChunks`, collapse threshold.

## Authoring

- **Hebrew only** — תקנית, פשוטה, מדוברת (see `docs/TEACHING_PRIMER_GUIDELINES.md` § עברית תקנית ופשוטה).
- **Single source:** edit `lib/content/teachingPrimerCatalog.ts` only (not duplicated in `day-*.ts`).
- Align with section worked example; run `teachingPrimerHebrewLint` via unit tests.
- **Length:** stay under `PRIMER_RECOMMENDED_COMBINED_CHARS` (850); collapse at 900 chars or >4 steps.

## TTS

- **Child profile** by default (`lib/tts/constants.ts` → `speakHebrew` / `speakHebrewChunks`).
- Primer: `TapToPlayTtsButton` with `chunks={buildDayPrimerSpeakChunks(day)}`.
- Exercises: single utterance via `buildExercisePromptSpeakText`.
- **No autoplay**; admin `ttsEnabled` gate.

## Test IDs

- `testIds.screen.dayOverview.teachingPrimer(grade, dayId)` — root `Surface`.
- Nested: `summary`, `steps`, `step.{idx}`, `teachingPrimerTts`, `teachingPrimerExpand`.

## Quality (mandatory when editing primer or TTS)

```bash
npm run test:unit -- tests/unit/lib/content/teaching-primer-content.test.ts
npm run test:unit -- tests/unit/lib/content/buildDayPrimerSpeakText.test.ts
npm run test:unit -- tests/unit/lib/tts/engine.test.ts
npm run test:unit -- tests/unit/lib/content/content-validity.test.ts
npm run test:e2e -- tests/e2e/day-smoke.spec.ts
npm run test:e2e -- tests/e2e/grade-b-lifecycle.spec.ts
npm run check:testids
```

Full release: `npm run test:qa`. Human checklist: `docs/TEACHING_PRIMER_GUIDELINES.md` § TTS verification.
